-- ON THE MOVE-Barclays hires two brokers in Florida
-- By Elizabeth Dilts
-- Tue Nov 18, 2014 05:48PM EST
-- None



NEW YORK, Nov 18 (Reuters) - Barclays <BARC.L> Wealth and Investment Management said Tuesday it hired two brokers, Josh Crossman and Ginny Neal, to join its Palm Beach, Florida office.

Ginny Neal joined Barclays in September from J.P. Morgan <JPM.N> Private Bank where she was a senior banker, according to a statement form Barclays. Josh Crossman also previously worked at J.P. Morgan, having left in May, according to records with the Financial Industry Regulatory Authority (FINRA). Crossman joined Barclays in October, according to FINRA. Barclays does not typically disclose advisers' individual production figures. Reuters covers advisers who manage more than $100 million in client assets.  With 12 offices in the U.S., Barclays focuses on high net worth clients.